flowRoot.flowPara: Rejected CGP (percentile 95 of genomic sample is greater than the number of paralogs in cluster candidate)
The analysis run successfully (can be used for parsing)
Number of paralogs per cluster (identified by the blastp and meanshift steps)

*Name of cluster candidate: the name of each cluster candidate has the following structure: <name_family>-<chromosome>_<sequential>, where <sequential> is an arbitrary number useful if there are multiple cluster candidates per chromosome**
Sample in the chromosome where the cluster candidate is located
Sampling results: The sampling results are reported using the structure sample_type (P95), where sample_type can be C or G, and P95 is the percentile 95 of each sample
